<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="transcription_factor_tf">Transcription Factor, TF</a> - A <a href="#protein">protein</a> that binds operator sequences in the <a href="#promoter">promoter</a> or <a href="#enhancer">enhancer</a> regions distal from the <a href="#promoter">promoter</a>. Activates or represses <a href="#transcription">transcription</a> depending on the presence of a <a href="#tad">trans-activation</a> or trans-repression domain, respectively. Also can contain a signal-sensing domain, which allows for external regulation of <a href="#dna_desoxyribonucleic_acid">DNA</a>-binding or cellular localisation, <em>exempli gratia</em> by small <a href="#molecule">molecules</a> or <a href="#hormone">hormones</a>.